HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 233
BY REPRESENTATIVE TERRY LANDRY
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates May 5, 2026, as Omega Psi Phi Day at the
Capitol
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Tuesday, May 5, 2026, as Omega Psi Phi Day at the Capitol.
3 WHEREAS, Omega Psi Phi Fraternity, Incorporated, was founded on November 17,
4 1911, at Howard University in Washington, D.C., by three visionary undergraduate students,
5 Edgar Amos Love, Oscar James Cooper, and Frank Coleman, and their faculty advisor,
6 Dr. Ernest Everett Just; and
7 WHEREAS, Omega Psi Phi was the first national fraternity to be established at a
8 historically Black university, and its name derives from the Greek phrase meaning
9 "friendship is essential to the soul", which also serves as the fraternity's motto; and
10 WHEREAS, from its inception, the fraternity has worked to build a strong and
11 effective force of men dedicated to the cardinal principles of Manhood, Scholarship,
12 Perseverance, and Uplift, and has given expression to the hopes and aspirations of an unfree
13 people in the land of the free; and
14 WHEREAS, Omega Psi Phi has chartered more than seven hundred fifty
15 undergraduate and graduate chapters and initiated more than two hundred fifty thousand men
16 into its brotherhood, with chapters operating across the United States and internationally;
17 and
18 WHEREAS, in 1930, Omega Psi Phi became one of five founding members of the
19 National Pan-Hellenic Council, which today is composed of nine international Black
20 Greek-letter sororities and fraternities and promotes cooperative programming and initiatives
21 for the benefit of African American communities; and
