1 WHEREAS, the Theta Kappa Chapter at Louisiana State University was chartered
2 on March 12, 1977, and became the first National Pan-Hellenic Council lettered fraternity
3 on the LSU campus; it is the founding chapter of LSU's National Pan-Hellenic Council and
4 stands as a trailblazer for Black Greek life in Baton Rouge; and
5 WHEREAS, May 5, 2026, marks the sixty-eighth anniversary of the founding of the
6 Delta Tau Chapter and is designated as Omega Psi Phi Fraternity, Incorporated, Day at the
7 state capitol; the day serves as a tribute to the chapter's decades of faithful service to the city
8 of Plaquemine, Iberville Parish, and the greater Baton Rouge area, and stewards the
9 fraternity's legacy across generations of brothers who have served as beacons of hope to their
10 community; and
11 WHEREAS, Omega Psi Phi chapters throughout Louisiana have continuously served
12 their communities through scholarship programs, voter registration drives, youth mentorship,
13 health initiatives, and civic engagement, embodying the fraternity's timeless cardinal
14 principles across generations; and
15 WHEREAS, the values of Omega Psi Phi Fraternity, Incorporated, are reflected in
16 the halls of the Legislature of Louisiana, where initiated brothers currently serve the people
17 of this state with distinction, including Senator James Harris, Senator Larry Selders,
18 Representative Marcus Bryant, Representative Kyle Green, Representative Rashid Young,
19 Representative Terry Landry Jr., and Representative Stephen Jackson; they each carry the
20 bond of brotherhood into their public service and their commitment to the betterment of all
21 Louisianans; and
22 WHEREAS, on May 5, 2026, members of Omega Psi Phi Fraternity, Incorporated,
23 from across the state of Louisiana gather at the state capitol to reaffirm their commitment
24 to service, brotherhood, and the uplift of all Louisianans and to celebrate the sixty-eighth
25 anniversary of the founding of the Delta Tau Chapter in Plaquemine.
26 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
27 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Tuesday, May 5, 2026, as Omega Psi Phi
28 Fraternity, Incorporated, Day at the state capitol; does hereby commend the brothers of
29 Omega Psi Phi for more than a century of distinguished service to the people of Louisiana
